import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['speed'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='speed', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['speed'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind speed?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='dir', y='speed', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind speed and wind direction?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['dir'] = data['dir'].astype(int)
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='dir', bins=36, kde=False)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind direction?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Wind Direction')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.axvline(data['dir'].mean(), color='red', label=f'Mean: {data["dir"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
